{
  "doc_id": "15588",
  "text": "We find that the BCJ numerators can be collected via a decomposition of the CHY form into a basis of integrals, which conceptually is similar to the aforementioned decomposition that string worldsheet integrals undergo. The CHY forms can be evaluated using Integration Rules and the cross-ratio method at tree and loop levels [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Recalling that the CHY form mathematically amounts to a multidimensional residue around the common zeros of the polynomial scattering equations, 1 the differential operator for evaluating such multidimensional residues proposed in our previous papers [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] comes in handy for evaluating and manipulating the CHY forms. Another method for computing multidimensional residues involving the Groebner basis or the H-basis is discussed in [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . A useful Mathematica package for computing such residues is given in [CITATION_9] .",
